37:09.345 --> 37:10.970
You can do all
the mewling you want

37:10.970 --> 37:12.887
about matters legal once I get
this copy locked in my safe.

37:12.887 --> 37:14.261
And then, Dad.

37:14.261 --> 37:16.136
You have to tell him everything.

37:16.136 --> 37:18.053
So he can defend us,
whatever may come.

37:18.053 --> 37:19.595
You mean about the idiot

37:19.595 --> 37:21.095
who stands to lose the most?

37:21.095 --> 37:22.887
Can I really...

37:22.887 --> 37:25.220
What the hell?

37:25.220 --> 37:26.845
We were just getting
to the good part...

37:26.845 --> 37:27.929
You know what the hell.

37:29.553 --> 37:31.720
There's no attorney-client
privilege with Krakow there.

37:31.720 --> 37:33.428
After Krakow leaves,

37:33.428 --> 37:35.387
Ira Schirmer clearly states
that he is their lawyer...

37:35.387 --> 37:37.637
In an exculpatory way for him,
I might add...

37:37.637 --> 37:39.345
And is about to give
legal advice.

37:39.345 --> 37:41.220
And so it was headphones off
for the agent

37:41.220 --> 37:42.261
and they killed the recording.

37:43.762 --> 37:45.261
So that... that was it,

37:45.261 --> 37:48.595
that was all he got
before he had to minimize?

37:48.595 --> 37:49.804
Roughly all.

37:49.804 --> 37:51.303
Fuck roughly.
What else did he get,

37:51.303 --> 37:52.595
what else is on
the unredacted tape?

37:52.595 --> 37:54.387
What, exactly, was getting
locked in the safe?

37:54.387 --> 37:56.178
Bryan! We talked about
this very fucking thing...

37:56.178 --> 37:58.428
Ohh. Come on, Kate.
This isn't fucking Girl Scouts.

37:58.428 --> 38:00.470
They were dancing around
whatever they were doing...

38:00.470 --> 38:02.053
If there's documentation
to be retrieved,

38:02.053 --> 38:03.470
the audio will get me a warrant.

38:03.470 --> 38:05.470
Stop pushing me.

38:05.470 --> 38:08.387
And you shouldn't even be
asking those questions.

38:08.387 --> 38:10.970
This is exactly
what I was afraid of.

38:15.970 --> 38:17.637
This meeting is over.

38:24.762 --> 38:27.345
Danny Margolis.

38:27.345 --> 38:30.804
You have done some good for me
in the not too distant past.

38:30.804 --> 38:32.178
And from what I hear,

38:32.178 --> 38:34.178
you made quite an impression
on those Feds.

38:34.178 --> 38:37.095
For the record it was chilly
that day by the pool.

38:37.095 --> 38:39.345
As I recall
it was positively balmy.

38:39.345 --> 38:41.136
But whatever you need
to tell yourself.

38:41.136 --> 38:43.512
Anyway, it motivated me
to tighten up my game.

38:43.512 --> 38:45.261
I'm working out like
six days a week now...

38:45.261 --> 38:46.970
Good for you.
Yeah.

38:46.970 --> 38:49.637
So. Business at hand.

38:49.637 --> 38:51.553
I believe I can do you
some more good, Axe.

38:51.553 --> 38:53.095
Let me tell you
what a freeport is...

38:53.095 --> 38:54.929
A storage facility
at a private airport

38:54.929 --> 38:57.136
where valuables purchased
overseas can be stored

38:57.136 --> 38:59.345
and deemed perpetually
'in transit' so the customs,

38:59.345 --> 39:01.845
duties and sales tax
can be avoided.

39:03.303 --> 39:05.136
So you do know...
Of course he does.

39:05.136 --> 39:07.136
But tell him the good part.

39:07.136 --> 39:09.512
I have one that I bought into.

39:09.512 --> 39:12.053
A freeport. Up in Newburgh,
private airstrip.

39:12.053 --> 39:13.637
Is that right?
Yeah.

39:13.637 --> 39:15.512
And I'm the commandant.

39:15.512 --> 39:17.845
So I can house your paintings
in a permanent tax-free state.

39:17.845 --> 39:19.679
That is of value.

39:19.679 --> 39:21.512
And I can do you
one even better:

39:21.512 --> 39:24.553
I'll store replicas,
so you can hang the originals.

39:24.553 --> 39:26.553
If anyone asks, you say
they're the replicas.

39:26.553 --> 39:28.887
For a small fee, of course.

39:28.887 --> 39:31.428
Medium fee?

39:31.428 --> 39:32.387
Okay.

39:32.387 --> 39:34.053
Stop talking.

39:34.053 --> 39:36.345
The rest gets worked out
between you and Victor.

39:36.345 --> 39:39.345
The shipment from Europe
will be rerouted to you.

39:39.345 --> 39:41.136
You let me know when I can
expect the 'replicas.'

39:48.345 --> 39:50.595
Hey.
You did well here.

39:50.595 --> 39:52.970
Keep it up.
Impress me.

39:52.970 --> 39:55.261
And soon enough you'll get off
the austerity plan.

39:55.261 --> 39:56.762
You can count on it.

40:06.303 --> 40:09.178
Now, that puts a bounce
in my man's step.

40:12.595 --> 40:15.428
Though I'm not sure I'd use
that room for that.

40:15.428 --> 40:16.845
Hard floor.

40:16.845 --> 40:19.053
Too hard.
And very public...

40:19.053 --> 40:20.595
She's not what you think she is.

40:32.845 --> 40:35.303
You need to know
that you might cry.

40:35.303 --> 40:39.095
And if you do,
that's just release.

40:39.095 --> 40:42.637
It means connection.

40:42.637 --> 40:46.136
It means freedom from
having to hold it all in.

40:46.136 --> 40:48.136
That sounds so good.

40:48.136 --> 40:49.970
How do we...

41:11.428 --> 41:13.679
She's a professional cuddler.

41:14.887 --> 41:16.553
And a star in her field.

41:37.220 --> 41:39.595
So...

41:39.595 --> 41:40.720
Hmm?

41:40.720 --> 41:42.804
Oh.
This our own cuddle session?

41:42.804 --> 41:45.553
No.
You already did the thing.

41:45.553 --> 41:48.845
Made me feel warm
and loved and cared for.

41:48.845 --> 41:51.845
Oh. Well, that's something
I don't hear every day.

41:51.845 --> 41:54.387
Look. I don't know if
Gordie really scraped his knee

41:54.387 --> 41:56.136
and Dean broke his surfboard...

41:56.136 --> 41:59.178
But you came back for me.

41:59.178 --> 42:02.387
As you would... and have... for me.

42:02.387 --> 42:04.637
It's more than touching, Axe.

42:04.637 --> 42:09.303
It's... compared to what I have
at this moment at home

42:09.303 --> 42:11.637
it's, uh... really nice.

42:11.637 --> 42:15.553
But also: you needed
to come back for you.

42:15.553 --> 42:18.512
For this...

42:18.512 --> 42:20.136
What about it?
They all fucked up.

42:20.136 --> 42:21.929
They needed to come in
and fix it.

42:21.929 --> 42:23.679
No. If it wasn't
today's reasons,

42:23.679 --> 42:25.387
you'd have come up with others.

42:25.387 --> 42:27.303
Okay.
I suppose I might've.

42:27.303 --> 42:29.053
You need to let them go home.

42:29.053 --> 42:31.595
Every single one of them.

42:31.595 --> 42:33.512
I don't like it.
If I'm here grinding,

42:33.512 --> 42:35.011
they should be here
grinding too.

42:35.011 --> 42:36.720
Yeah. You can't let yourself
take a day off,

42:36.720 --> 42:38.011
so they can't take a day off.

42:38.011 --> 42:39.929
So you can surround yourself.

42:39.929 --> 42:44.470
Okay. Maybe I want
the edge they'll get me.

42:44.470 --> 42:46.428
Maybe I want them to
regain their own edge.

42:46.428 --> 42:47.679
Maybe I want them
to feel the opposite

42:47.679 --> 42:50.303
of the way Wags does right now...

42:50.303 --> 42:52.929
Totally uncomfortable in
their position and place,

42:52.929 --> 42:55.720
scared to death of
my disapproval, of failing,

42:55.720 --> 42:57.470
of not being exactly
where I need them to be

42:57.470 --> 42:59.053
exactly when I need them there.

42:59.053 --> 43:00.720
Many of them thrive
under those conditions.

43:00.720 --> 43:03.428
For long bursts.
But then they need to recover.

43:03.428 --> 43:04.720
On my time?

43:04.720 --> 43:06.762
It's not all your time.
It's a holiday.

43:06.762 --> 43:09.595
There are no holidays
when it's my money.

43:09.595 --> 43:10.929
They are rich because of me.

43:10.929 --> 43:12.845
So they can help me
stay that way.

43:12.845 --> 43:15.595
You're punishing them
because they're not you.

43:15.595 --> 43:18.303
You need to let them
go home, Bobby.

43:18.303 --> 43:20.804
So they can come back tomorrow
and actually work.

43:20.804 --> 43:22.804
What's the point of
any of you being rich

43:22.804 --> 43:24.387
if you can't fucking enjoy it.

43:24.387 --> 43:26.804
I'll let you know when I do...

43:30.970 --> 43:33.679
This...

43:33.679 --> 43:35.136
Yeah.

43:35.136 --> 43:39.387
This is why I can't let you
lose that hearing.

43:39.387 --> 43:42.136
Because I have always known

43:42.136 --> 43:45.470
I need you more than
anyone else here.

43:45.470 --> 43:47.637
At least I have since...

43:47.637 --> 43:50.178
Have I ever told you

43:50.178 --> 43:53.804
why and when, exactly,

43:53.804 --> 43:57.637
I knew that you were gonna be
my partner at all this. Forever.

43:57.637 --> 43:59.095
You remember?

43:59.095 --> 44:01.929
What kind of man would I be
if I didn't?

44:01.929 --> 44:04.929
Mnh.

44:08.178 --> 44:10.011
Well, this was
the one time in my life

44:10.011 --> 44:13.220
I wasn't able to fight for
myself, and you fought for me.

44:13.220 --> 44:15.178
Well. I'm sure you didn't
let on that was the case.

44:15.178 --> 44:16.970
Whenever this was.

44:16.970 --> 44:19.595
Yeah. But you knew.

44:19.595 --> 44:22.720
It was right after 9/11.

44:22.720 --> 44:25.762
When I'd made the bold
but foolhardy statement

44:25.762 --> 44:27.970
that I would take care of
all the survivors,

44:27.970 --> 44:31.011
and the families
of those who didn't.

44:31.011 --> 44:34.804
And that I'd not only find a way
to pay for every funeral,

44:34.804 --> 44:37.011
put every kid through school,

44:37.011 --> 44:40.053
but that I'd also pay out
all the bonuses too,

44:40.053 --> 44:41.428
for the next three years.

44:41.428 --> 44:43.512
It wasn't foolhardy.
It was generous.

44:43.512 --> 44:45.220
It was the best of you.

44:45.220 --> 44:47.637
Sure.
But also: impossible.

44:47.637 --> 44:51.428
Every business advisor I had

44:51.428 --> 44:53.470
told me to
shut down the company.

44:53.470 --> 44:56.720
Act of God.
Nothing for me to do.

44:56.720 --> 44:58.845
I mean, we had no book,
we had no personnel.

44:58.845 --> 45:00.345
We were facing margin calls.

45:00.345 --> 45:02.220
Every bank insisted
I let it die.

45:02.220 --> 45:03.845
But you didn't listen.

45:03.845 --> 45:05.512
You'd been awake for, what,
three weeks straight?

45:05.512 --> 45:06.887
Mm.

45:06.887 --> 45:08.470
I remember wondering
how you were doing it.

45:08.470 --> 45:11.011
How you stayed so lucid.

45:11.011 --> 45:12.804
I didn't feel it.

45:12.804 --> 45:16.261
You still don't know
the moment, do you?

45:16.261 --> 45:18.887
I... don't.

45:18.887 --> 45:20.136
It's all such a...

45:20.136 --> 45:22.220
Yeah. It was a blur.

45:22.220 --> 45:24.679
Except for the few
that stand out.

45:24.679 --> 45:26.762
This was at one of the funerals.

45:26.762 --> 45:29.679
God. For a while that was
our days, right?

45:29.679 --> 45:31.970
Going down to Ground Zero
in the morning,

45:31.970 --> 45:33.428
funeral in the afternoon,

45:33.428 --> 45:36.804
then arguing with banks
and investors, you know,

45:36.804 --> 45:41.178
every hour into the night,
to try to save the company.

45:41.178 --> 45:42.720
I mean, look.

45:42.720 --> 45:44.261
I knew that I'd locked in
a windfall.

45:44.261 --> 45:46.011
But it hadn't been
repatriated yet.

45:46.011 --> 45:48.553
Back then, I was still
just on loan to you guys

45:48.553 --> 45:50.428
from that sports psych place
I worked at.

45:50.428 --> 45:52.720
Yeah. We used to do
the funerals together.

45:52.720 --> 45:54.553
You would help
with the families.

45:54.553 --> 45:56.679
And then at this one funeral,

45:56.679 --> 46:00.679
I got bum rushed by
this group of families.

46:00.679 --> 46:03.428
Who told me I wasn't getting
them all paid fast enough.

46:03.428 --> 46:06.011
They attacked my integrity.
They called me a thief.

46:06.011 --> 46:07.512
Said I was stealing money
from them.

46:07.512 --> 46:09.136
When all I was fucking doing

46:09.136 --> 46:13.053
was arguing and scheming

46:13.053 --> 46:17.637
just to keep the firm going
to give them their money.

46:17.637 --> 46:20.220
Normally, I'd have...
I'd have fought it.

46:20.220 --> 46:24.428
But

46:24.428 --> 46:28.387
right at that moment,

46:28.387 --> 46:30.595
it all just became too much.

46:30.595 --> 46:32.220
Of course.

46:32.220 --> 46:35.428
The grief, the sleeplessness,
the survivor's guilt,

46:35.428 --> 46:38.178
the impossibility of the task...

46:38.178 --> 46:41.220
I just stood there,
as they unloaded on me.

46:41.220 --> 46:43.512
I was struck dumb.

46:43.512 --> 46:45.762
And then the whole place
started watching.

46:45.762 --> 46:48.512
It almost turned into
a mob situation.

46:48.512 --> 46:49.762
And that is when...

46:49.762 --> 46:52.345
I stepped in between
them and you.

46:54.136 --> 46:55.345
I remember now.

46:55.345 --> 46:56.387
You sure did.

46:56.387 --> 46:57.804
You remember what you said?

46:57.804 --> 46:59.637
'Cause I remember every word.

46:59.637 --> 47:01.845
Loud enough for the whole place
to hear:

47:01.845 --> 47:05.345
"Shut the fuck up.

47:05.345 --> 47:08.345
You lost family.
So did everyone else here.

47:08.345 --> 47:10.929
And this man is the only hope
you... or any of you...

47:10.929 --> 47:13.095
Have of paying for
the rest of your lives.

47:13.095 --> 47:16.679
And I'll tell you another thing,
I have begged him not to.

47:16.679 --> 47:20.178
Because I think
it'll destroy him next.

47:20.178 --> 47:21.553
He doesn't need it.

47:21.553 --> 47:24.887
He can move on clean
and in a couple of years

47:24.887 --> 47:27.220
he'll have enough wealth
for twenty lifetimes.

47:27.220 --> 47:29.387
But if he's really
too slow for you,

47:29.387 --> 47:31.428
if you really think that
he is stealing from you,

47:31.428 --> 47:34.679
say another word, and I will
make him shut it down.

47:34.679 --> 47:38.053
Otherwise,
shake his fucking hand,

47:38.053 --> 47:41.428
say thank you,
and we can all mourn together."

47:41.428 --> 47:43.387
And that's just what happened...

47:44.887 --> 47:46.762
But that's not the moment.

47:46.762 --> 47:48.720
The moment is when
you got to my car after.

47:48.720 --> 47:49.762
And you said...

47:49.762 --> 47:52.053
I said, "Bobby,

47:52.053 --> 47:54.845
you better fucking deliver
for those people.

47:54.845 --> 47:56.428
Or I won't just make you quit.

47:56.428 --> 47:57.679
I'll kill you myself."

47:57.679 --> 48:00.053
And right then

48:00.053 --> 48:02.804
I knew that you were my partner
in this for life.

48:02.804 --> 48:07.387
Because you were loyal to me
in the face of the world,

48:07.387 --> 48:09.387
but in private
you held me to account

48:09.387 --> 48:11.762
and you were loyal
to the bigger cause.

48:11.762 --> 48:13.178
And you were fun as hell
to watch.

48:13.178 --> 48:14.595
And you still are.

48:14.595 --> 48:17.929
So you say whatever you need
in that hearing

48:17.929 --> 48:19.428
to get you out of this.

48:19.428 --> 48:22.845
And I will back you to
the ends of the earth on it.

48:30.011 --> 48:31.553
I hope I can.

48:34.261 --> 48:37.804
And if you can't,
you got to do the other thing.

48:37.804 --> 48:39.929
The other thing?

48:39.929 --> 48:42.178
You have the power
to make this go away.

48:42.178 --> 48:45.053
So that you don't have to
defend yourself in that hearing.

48:45.053 --> 48:48.136
I heard you earlier,
that Taylor can't be moved.

48:48.136 --> 48:51.679
And if it was me trying,
then you'd probably be right...

48:51.679 --> 48:56.303
But as much as it kills me
to suggest:

48:56.303 --> 48:57.512
Go to Taylor.

48:57.512 --> 48:59.095
Talk to them.

48:59.095 --> 49:02.887
And ask for their forgiveness.

49:11.095 --> 49:14.512
Right.

49:22.387 --> 49:23.804
Oh. You look zenned out.

49:23.804 --> 49:25.470
Enjoy your hug?

49:25.470 --> 49:27.512
Oh, she gives
far more than that.

49:27.512 --> 49:30.470
She imparts a total sense
of well-being.

49:32.387 --> 49:34.595
Ah. Ben Kim!
Lookit that.

49:34.595 --> 49:36.762
The only one to
come in voluntarily.

49:36.762 --> 49:38.970
I do this every year.

49:38.970 --> 49:41.804
I sit at my desk,
alone, visualize

49:41.804 --> 49:43.345
and do my goal setting
for the year.

49:43.345 --> 49:44.887
Of course you do.

49:44.887 --> 49:49.428
Ben, my boy, you're not
doing it alone this year.

49:49.428 --> 49:52.261
Come on.

49:52.261 --> 49:54.553
I guess Ben Kim's
gonna get cuddled.

49:57.845 --> 49:59.512
Hey.

49:59.512 --> 50:00.804
Good luck.

50:06.428 --> 50:09.011
Ok everyone!
I love the effort.

50:09.011 --> 50:10.804
And seeing your beautiful
fucking faces.

50:10.804 --> 50:12.679
But you've done enough.

50:12.679 --> 50:17.136
So fuck off out of here and
enjoy the rest of your holiday.

50:17.136 --> 50:18.887
Now, when you get home,

50:18.887 --> 50:20.887
you will find a case
of champagne from me.

50:20.887 --> 50:22.804
And a tin of caviar.

50:22.804 --> 50:25.220
You'll have to order
your own pizza, okay?

50:25.220 --> 50:26.720
So, eat up, drink up.

50:26.720 --> 50:29.220
And then get yourselves ready
to get back here

50:29.220 --> 50:30.970
for when the market opens

50:30.970 --> 50:34.220
ready to motherfucking
destroy for me.

50:39.720 --> 50:40.720
Come on!

51:04.428 --> 51:06.762
I really thought
we were done with this.

51:06.762 --> 51:08.512
One last conversation.

51:08.512 --> 51:10.220
One last ask?

51:11.845 --> 51:14.178
Are you hoping I just don't
show up to the Med Board

51:14.178 --> 51:16.095
or are you going to
ask me not to?

51:16.095 --> 51:18.970
Whichever.

51:18.970 --> 51:23.261
Look.
All I want to say is:

51:23.261 --> 51:25.804
I'm sorry.

51:25.804 --> 51:30.220
I am truly sorry.

51:30.220 --> 51:32.887
Some kind of desire for revenge,

51:32.887 --> 51:36.470
or competitiveness, or bloodlust

51:36.470 --> 51:38.220
got a hold of me
and let me go too far.

51:38.220 --> 51:42.887
No, I... I
let myself go too far.

51:42.887 --> 51:45.178
I'd say way too fucking far.

51:45.178 --> 51:49.428
But know this:

51:49.428 --> 51:51.470
you say you don't want to
end up like Axe. Or me.

51:51.470 --> 51:55.095
Well, that's where this
kind of vengeance leads.

51:55.095 --> 52:00.261
It's ugly, it's sickening

52:00.261 --> 52:03.178
and I don't recommend it,
to my worst enemy.

52:03.178 --> 52:05.470
Much less someone I once
cared so much for,

52:05.470 --> 52:09.470
and... and still, oddly do.

52:09.470 --> 52:12.762
Your apology isn't real.

52:12.762 --> 52:14.178
Do I need to impress upon you

52:14.178 --> 52:16.428
how much my medical license
means to me?

52:16.428 --> 52:19.720
This, like everything with you,
is now merely transactional.

52:19.720 --> 52:21.679
That's who and what you are.

52:21.679 --> 52:24.053
So you have to actually
ask me not to show up.

52:24.053 --> 52:25.512
As a personal favor to you.

52:25.512 --> 52:27.261
You have to say the words.

52:27.261 --> 52:31.845
Please don't come
to the hearing.

52:31.845 --> 52:34.303
Do that for me.

52:34.303 --> 52:37.345
You are torn up, Wendy.

52:37.345 --> 52:39.887
The look in your eye tells me
that there is still,

52:39.887 --> 52:43.428
somewhere inside of you, someone
who knows right from wrong.

52:43.428 --> 52:45.595
This hearing is your chance
to reclaim that person.

52:45.595 --> 52:47.261
I am not setting you up
for defeat.

52:47.261 --> 52:49.470
I am giving you a chance
to save yourself.

52:54.303 --> 52:57.011
And, in fact, that decides it.

52:57.011 --> 52:58.220
I won't come to the hearing.

52:58.220 --> 53:00.845
If you think you should
keep your license

53:00.845 --> 53:04.303
so you can continue to
treat people, tell them why.

53:04.303 --> 53:06.345
And I won't be there
to tell them any different.

53:11.637 --> 53:14.428
I will.
Thank you.

53:14.428 --> 53:16.053
I owe you one.

53:16.053 --> 53:18.387
You do.

53:18.387 --> 53:20.887
But you owe yourself even more.

53:45.470 --> 53:47.345
Come on.
Seriously?

53:47.345 --> 53:48.845
No. No. No. No. No.
You're doing this.

53:48.845 --> 53:52.387
You can. And will.

53:54.470 --> 53:55.762
You know what this symbol is?

53:55.762 --> 53:57.095
Yeah. Divine wind.

53:57.095 --> 53:58.929
Kamikaze. Right?

53:58.929 --> 54:00.387
Who made the ultimate sacrifice

54:00.387 --> 54:02.261
for their emperor,
their nation, their ideals.

54:02.261 --> 54:04.345
But the board?
The metaphor I get,

54:04.345 --> 54:07.095
but this isn't... it's not
kids' karate class.

54:07.095 --> 54:08.762
Go beyond the metaphor.

54:08.762 --> 54:10.345
Break through it.

54:10.345 --> 54:12.261
Feel it.

54:17.261 --> 54:18.720
Hyah!

54:18.720 --> 54:20.261
Do you see that?

54:20.261 --> 54:23.553
Do you see, Bryan,
nothing makes you feel

54:23.553 --> 54:27.095
the purest version of yourself
more than going kamikaze.

54:27.095 --> 54:30.387
I want you to make
an all-out attack on success.

54:30.387 --> 54:31.637
Hmm.

54:31.637 --> 54:33.387
The kamikaze get a bad name

54:33.387 --> 54:36.053
because everyone wants
to focus on the suicide.

54:36.053 --> 54:38.220
But what they miss out on

54:38.220 --> 54:41.720
is the purity of the commitment.

54:41.720 --> 54:43.011
Hmm.

54:43.011 --> 54:44.470
Good.

54:48.679 --> 54:50.303
Again!

54:50.303 --> 54:51.679
Ah!
Yeah!

54:51.679 --> 54:52.720
Yeah!
Ah!

54:52.720 --> 54:54.303
Yeah!
Yeah!

54:54.303 --> 54:56.679
Oh! One more!

55:06.637 --> 55:08.637
You figure out your strategy?

55:08.637 --> 55:12.595
Things were done,
moves were made.

55:12.595 --> 55:15.136
Good.

55:15.136 --> 55:17.553
And your thing?

55:17.553 --> 55:20.804
Productive.

55:20.804 --> 55:23.428
Great.

55:27.804 --> 55:31.720
Chuck, when did you know
you needed to marry me?

55:34.011 --> 55:38.762
I mean the... the exact moment

55:38.762 --> 55:41.011
and why.

55:48.178 --> 55:49.929
One single moment?
Uh...

55:56.220 --> 55:58.887
...I don't remember.

56:08.053 --> 56:10.679
Hey, kids! Dinner!

56:43.261 --> 56:44.428
...sipping
fucking Jamesons

56:44.428 --> 56:46.428
in your fancy fucking jeans

56:46.428 --> 56:48.887
and your hundred dollar haircuts
and your BMWs.

56:48.887 --> 56:51.929
You only remember you're Irish
on St. Paddy's Day and Easter.

56:51.929 --> 56:53.387
Believe this guy?

56:53.387 --> 56:55.136
You know what? Fuck...

57:02.720 --> 57:04.387
Don't even fucking
think about it.

57:04.387 --> 57:06.428
Ah, what the fuck, Jackie?

57:06.428 --> 57:08.720
He fell.

57:08.720 --> 57:09.762
Both of 'em?

57:09.762 --> 57:11.303
They're fucking clumsy.

57:11.303 --> 57:13.595
Bryan. Get your brother
outta here, would ya?

57:13.595 --> 57:16.220
'So you know: I had those fake
fucking Irish pricks...

57:16.220 --> 57:17.762
Yeah, course you did.

57:17.762 --> 57:19.345
And when was the last time
you've been over in Belfast

57:19.345 --> 57:20.970
supporting the cause?
Well. That'd be never.

57:20.970 --> 57:22.345
C'mon...

57:22.345 --> 57:25.303
Yeah, but I did
go to Cape Cod once...

57:28.053 --> 57:32.303
So, baby brother,

57:32.303 --> 57:34.136
haven't seen you in years.

57:34.136 --> 57:36.136
'Cause you don't come to Ma's
for Christmas anymore.

57:36.136 --> 57:38.303
I don't like her ham...

57:38.303 --> 57:41.387
But you suddenly
showing up here...

57:41.387 --> 57:43.178
Must mean you want something.

57:45.637 --> 57:47.720
What is it you want?

57:47.720 --> 57:50.512
The one thing you do with those
hands better than fight.

57:53.261 --> 57:55.053
There's a safe?

57:55.053 --> 57:57.887
You bet your ass there is.

